      "description": "Honest project car with solid mechanical bones and plenty of potential. It starts, runs, and offers a strong platform for someone who knows their way around maintenance and sorting. The powertrain feels willing, the chassis is complete, and it has the kind of straightforward, serviceable character enthusiasts look for in a budget build, commuter revival, or parts donor with real upside. Cosmetic wear, age-related flaws, and general roughness are present, so come expecting a driver-quality project rather than a polished example. If you want an affordable entry point with usable fundamentals and room to improve, this one makes a compelling case.",
